The state capture inquiry commission will continue to hear Senior Hawks Investigator Kobus Roelofse testimony JOHANNESBURG - The State Capture Commission will continue to hear Senior Hawks Investigator Kobus Roelofse's testimony on Thursday. READ: Crime intelligence's piggy bank detailed at Zondo Commission Roelofse's Wednesday testimony detailed alleged criminal activity within crime intelligence structures, starting at the very top. Roelofse has told the inquiry his attempts to investigate were often obstructed. A lot of Roelofse’s testimony focused on a crime intelligence slush fund, stocked with public money, and run like a private piggy bank.